1
00:00:03,962 --> 00:00:08,091
(Episode 5: Shall We Begin Starting Today?)

2
00:00:24,524 --> 00:00:27,764
Shall we begin starting today? (TN: Can
also mean "Should we start dating today?")

3
00:01:13,156 --> 00:01:16,658
Ugh, seriously, how does
a sandwich taste fishy?

4
00:01:16,659 --> 00:01:18,870
Can't you just eat what you're given?

5
00:01:25,585 --> 00:01:28,191
The owner of the site we
plan to purchase in Seoil-dong

6
00:01:28,215 --> 00:01:30,631
has stated they intend
to raise their asking price.

7
00:01:30,632 --> 00:01:33,843
I believe you need to
review this matter.

8
00:01:38,723 --> 00:01:40,891
What are your thoughts, Secretary Ha?

9
00:01:40,892 --> 00:01:44,436
It seems we need to renegotiate the
purchase terms and review alternative sites.

10
00:01:44,437 --> 00:01:45,479
Proceed with that.

11
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:49,942
Also, regarding the land in Hooyeon-dong,
the buyer has requested a price reduction.

12
00:01:49,943 --> 00:01:51,402
For this, we should...

13
00:01:57,659 --> 00:02:00,285
It's all dirty now!
Get out.

14
00:02:00,286 --> 00:02:01,703
- Just my stuff, just my stuff!
- No, get out!

15
00:02:01,704 --> 00:02:03,539
Get out, you keep making
dirty footprints everywhere.

16
00:02:03,540 --> 00:02:05,290
Hurry up and get out, out!

17
00:02:05,291 --> 00:02:08,691
I just asked for some local tourist spots.
Does it make sense that you don't know any?

18
00:02:08,878 --> 00:02:10,504
Why wouldn't it make sense?

19
00:02:10,505 --> 00:02:12,548
Aren't you supposed to
figure out your own trip?

20
00:02:12,549 --> 00:02:13,925
Seriously...

21
00:02:34,237 --> 00:02:36,447
What happened with the Seoil-dong purchase?

22
00:02:37,532 --> 00:02:39,867
- Ah...
- Still...?

23
00:02:39,868 --> 00:02:42,369
Didn't you send it?
It didn't go through?

24
00:02:42,370 --> 00:02:45,832
Bring me some profit right now,
you useless jerk!

25
00:02:49,544 --> 00:02:51,588
Should we accept their terms?

26
00:02:51,963 --> 00:02:54,715
That won't make us any money.
We need to generate a profit.

27
00:02:54,716 --> 00:02:57,968
In that case...
Could you review this one?

28
00:02:57,969 --> 00:03:00,305
This won't make money either.

29
00:03:01,890 --> 00:03:04,392
And neither will this!

30
00:03:05,435 --> 00:03:07,394
Please take a look at this too.

31
00:03:07,395 --> 00:03:09,814
There's no money here, absolutely no money.

32
00:03:10,189 --> 00:03:11,399
Ah...

33
00:03:42,931 --> 00:03:46,684
Well, there's a good dessert place nearby,
so I thought you should try it.

34
00:03:47,227 --> 00:03:49,187
And I'm sorry for getting mad yesterday.

35
00:04:14,170 --> 00:04:16,005
It might be difficult at first glance.

36
00:04:17,757 --> 00:04:20,843
When I first learned this,
this was the hardest part too.

37
00:04:21,261 --> 00:04:24,137
"Regulations on Housing
Construction Standards."

38
00:04:24,138 --> 00:04:26,848
This means that
when installing a parking lot in a complex,

39
00:04:26,849 --> 00:04:31,436
you must install parking spaces that exceed
the calculated minimum requirement.

40
00:04:31,437 --> 00:04:34,857
Exactly how many spaces are needed
is something Secretary Ha will know.

41
00:04:47,453 --> 00:04:48,871
It's a begonia.

42
00:04:49,998 --> 00:04:52,041
The seeds must have
blown in from somewhere.

43
00:04:54,669 --> 00:04:55,795
A begonia?

44
00:04:56,254 --> 00:04:57,297
Yes.

45
00:04:57,547 --> 00:05:00,340
They say it's a sign that
something good is about to happen.

46
00:05:00,341 --> 00:05:02,426
Looks like something good will happen soon.

47
00:05:02,427 --> 00:05:07,098
There you go saying nonsense again.
That's all superstition and delusion.

48
00:05:07,390 --> 00:05:09,058
You have no sense of romance.

49
00:05:09,726 --> 00:05:11,727
How is it? Working here?

50
00:05:11,728 --> 00:05:13,062
Annoying.

51
00:05:13,354 --> 00:05:14,605
But...

52
00:05:15,898 --> 00:05:17,525
It's not bad.

53
00:05:20,675 --> 00:05:22,613
It's terrible for me...

54
00:05:22,905 --> 00:05:26,199
I finally understand why you're
always obsessed with money, Boss.

55
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:28,785
It's impossible not to get a bad temper.

56
00:05:28,786 --> 00:05:29,786
What?

57
00:05:30,121 --> 00:05:33,333
Want to go see the ocean?
To clear our heads.

58
00:05:35,543 --> 00:05:36,794
Sure.

59
00:05:38,546 --> 00:05:39,672
Hmph.

60
00:06:00,735 --> 00:06:04,739
Five years ago...
I made a decision after seeing this ocean.

61
00:06:05,990 --> 00:06:07,533
To stay here.

62
00:06:09,202 --> 00:06:10,912
What did you do five years ago?

63
00:06:12,497 --> 00:06:16,542
I worked at a company in Seoul. Believe it
or not, I worked for a major corporation!

64
00:06:19,045 --> 00:06:24,967
That ocean doesn't look special enough
to throw all that away and come here...

65
00:06:28,805 --> 00:06:31,099
It's a magical place.

66
00:06:32,517 --> 00:06:36,979
Five years ago...
When I first came here.

67
00:06:37,688 --> 00:06:41,984
I barely managed to get some time off
from being swamped with work.

68
00:06:43,319 --> 00:06:46,572
I ended up staying at Badam Stay by chance.

69
00:06:47,698 --> 00:06:53,913
On the second day, my boss opened
the guesthouse door and walked in.

70
00:06:56,165 --> 00:06:58,876
He was someone who tormented me constantly.

71
00:07:00,294 --> 00:07:04,132
It turns out he came to
the exact same place for his vacation.

72
00:07:06,425 --> 00:07:10,930
That night,
do you know what he told me?

73
00:07:12,890 --> 00:07:14,100
What did he say?

74
00:07:16,310 --> 00:07:18,104
That he was sorry.

75
00:07:19,730 --> 00:07:21,774
That he had no choice.

76
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:30,031
This is a magical place.

77
00:07:30,032 --> 00:07:32,326
The kind of magic that changes people.

78
00:07:35,371 --> 00:07:37,540
Magic that changes people...

79
00:07:39,667 --> 00:07:44,422
Such special feelings
are nothing in the face of money anyway.

80
00:07:48,759 --> 00:07:51,022
You were crying because your favorite bookstore

81
00:07:51,046 --> 00:07:53,890
disappeared due to redevelopment. That's when I told you...

82
00:07:55,349 --> 00:07:58,978
What kind of place
was the bookstore your mother mentioned?

83
00:08:03,816 --> 00:08:08,404
I told you yesterday. This is a
place to share a chat with the sea.

84
00:08:09,447 --> 00:08:12,783
It's okay to open up and speak your mind.

85
00:08:16,871 --> 00:08:18,080
Geez...

86
00:08:20,291 --> 00:08:23,920
Fine, I'll play along and tell you.

87
00:08:24,253 --> 00:08:26,923
When I was young, I
wanted to be a novelist.

88
00:08:28,257 --> 00:08:31,761
Of course, my mother was against it.

89
00:08:33,763 --> 00:08:36,557
I went to a secondhand bookstore every day
behind my mother's back.

90
00:08:37,225 --> 00:08:40,478
The owner was someone
who genuinely loved books,

91
00:08:41,562 --> 00:08:44,440
and he told me I could come
and read whenever I wanted.

92
00:08:47,527 --> 00:08:50,946
It was the only place
where I could dream...

93
00:08:50,947 --> 00:08:53,949
- These books...
- It was a precious place.

94
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:59,163
hold a value so great that I
wouldn't trade them for a fortune.

95
00:08:59,538 --> 00:09:00,915
But...

96
00:09:02,458 --> 00:09:05,711
The bookstore building was demolished
due to redevelopment,

97
00:09:06,379 --> 00:09:10,049
and while I was grieving,
my mother said to me...

98
00:09:10,883 --> 00:09:16,138
Once a high-rise is built here,
its value will multiply tenfold.

99
00:09:16,472 --> 00:09:21,602
Numbers, not emotions,
will protect your future.

100
00:09:24,355 --> 00:09:25,815
Since then...

101
00:09:27,024 --> 00:09:29,527
I don't believe in any
value other than money.

102
00:09:31,487 --> 00:09:32,822
I see.

103
00:09:33,614 --> 00:09:35,740
My mother was right.

104
00:09:35,741 --> 00:09:37,076
Numbers...

105
00:09:37,952 --> 00:09:39,287
Money...

106
00:09:40,162 --> 00:09:42,248
That's what will protect my future.

107
00:09:42,999 --> 00:09:45,626
What if money can't protect you?

108
00:09:46,794 --> 00:09:47,753
What?

109
00:09:47,754 --> 00:09:50,881
What if money
is what actually torments you?

110
00:09:53,634 --> 00:09:55,886
Try valuing yourself more.

111
00:09:56,470 --> 00:10:01,017
Then, even the most ordinary things
will become special.

112
00:10:07,356 --> 00:10:08,399
Ah.

113
00:10:09,191 --> 00:10:10,901
And Boss, you're mine.

114
00:10:11,652 --> 00:10:12,652
Huh?

115
00:10:13,571 --> 00:10:15,989
I'm stepping on your shadow.

116
00:10:15,990 --> 00:10:17,950
Your soul belongs to me.

117
00:10:19,952 --> 00:10:21,579
What's with you all of a sudden?

118
00:10:21,954 --> 00:10:23,539
Playing shadow tag so childishly...

119
00:10:24,582 --> 00:10:26,125
Oh yeah, mine again!

120
00:10:26,917 --> 00:10:27,960
Hey!

121
00:11:30,189 --> 00:11:36,696
"Check In to You"
